1. Artifacts produced by ML
The ML will deliver five files.
These constitute the only inputs required by backend.

✅ 1. user_emb.npy

Shape: (num_users, embedding_dim)

Type: float32 NumPy array

Contains user tower output vectors.

✅ 2. item_emb.npy

Shape: (num_items, embedding_dim)

Type: float32 NumPy array

Contains item tower output vectors.

✅ 3. uid2idx.json

Mapping file:

{
  "A3FXXXXXX": 0,
  "A1ZXXXXXX": 1
}

Maps original user_id → row index in user_emb.npy.

✅ 4. iid2idx.json

Mapping file:

{
  "B0001234": 0,
  "B07XXXXXX": 1
}


Maps item_id → row index in item_emb.npy.

✅ 5. items_meta.parquet

A table containing metadata for each item index:

item_id	title	image_url	category	brand	…
B01ABC	…	…	…	…	

Note: Row order must match item_emb.npy.

2. Where These Files Are Stored
Machine Learning Core/results/models/

3. Backend responsibility

Backend exists under:

Backend API/backend/app/

Backend is responsible for:

Loading the embeddings & metadata

Building or loading a FAISS index

Implementing recall logic

Exposing REST APIs

Serving data to frontend

4. Frontend Integration
Frontend should display:

product image

title

score

userid